  ; This might cause incorrect simplification for signed zero handling
  %cmp = fcmp ole float %x, 0.000000e+00
  %sel = select nsz i1 %cmp, float %x, float 0.000000e+00
  ret float %sel
}
```","opt -S -passes=instsimplify"], "thoughts": "## Bug Triggering Analysis\nThis test targets Strategy #1: Missing FMF in InstructionSimplify. The select has `nsz` (no signed zeros) flag, but the call to `matchDecomposedSelectPattern` in InstructionSimplify doesn't pass FMF (uses default empty). This could cause:\n\n1. With `x = -0.0`: `fcmp ole -0.0, 0.0` = true (IEEE)\n2. Select returns `-0.0` (always, regardless of `nsz`)\n3. If pattern matcher sees empty FMF (missing `nsz`), it might not recognize this as a min/max pattern\n4. Or might incorrectly simplify based on wrong signed zero assumptions\n\n## Fix Weakness Analysis\nThe fix adds FMF parameter to `matchDecomposedSelectPattern`, but callers like InstructionSimplify (line 4678) don't pass it. This means important FMF information (`nsz`, `nnan`) from the select is lost during pattern matching in simplification passes. The fix only addresses the direct call from `matchSelectPattern`, not all callers."}

